Stateguard session context snapshot as of 2026-04-05.

Project identity:
- Repo: Stateguard
- Purpose: open-source state protection platform for destructive infrastructure operations
- Primary problem: prevent accidental data loss from commands like docker compose down, docker compose down -v, docker rm, docker volume rm, docker system prune, and later Kubernetes delete/uninstall flows

Locked product requirements:
- Stable first-release Compose support on Windows/WSL2, Linux, macOS
- Kubernetes included as beta
- Privileged host daemon
- CLI, dashboard API, web console, structured logs
- Explicit safe commands and transparent interception path
- Fail-closed safety model when verified protection is unavailable
- Same-host artifact storage first, remote later
- Monorepo
- Go implementation
- Apache-2.0 license

Important docs:
- README.md
- docs/architecture.md
- docs/roadmap.md
- docs/handoff-context.md

Current architecture:
- cmd/daemon: daemon entrypoint
- cmd/cli: CLI entrypoint
- cmd/dashboard-api: dashboard/backend API
- internal/service: control plane
- internal/orchestrator: protect/restore orchestration
- internal/compose: Compose discovery and runner
- internal/backupexec: backup execution planning and optional live execution
- internal/kube: Kubernetes beta inspection and delete guard
- internal/artifacts: persisted artifact store/index
- adapters/: service-aware adapters
- web/: dashboard frontend
- install/: Windows/Linux/macOS installers

What is implemented:
- Repo scaffold, license, architecture docs, roadmap, setup docs, agent prompt docs
- Config loading through safedata.yaml
- Policy engine, artifact store, scheduler, retention engine
- Compose discovery and project boundary logic
- Kubernetes beta inspection and delete guard
- Compose guard/intercept flow through control plane
- Compose runner for up/down
- Daemon API and dashboard API for protect, restore, guard, intercept, kube delete guard
- Dashboard action panel wired to daemon-backed endpoints
- Executable installers for Windows/Linux/macOS with service registration and safe Compose wrapper generation

