Current interception/completion state:
- raw Docker argument interception now exists for Compose-scoped destructive intent
- current parser supports:
  - docker compose -f <file> down
  - docker compose -f <file> down -v
  - docker compose -f <file> up
  - docker volume rm
  - docker system prune
- raw volume/system prune is evaluated and explicitly not auto-executed yet because higher-order scope mapping is still needed

Current Kubernetes state:
- inspect
- protect
- guard-delete
- enforce-delete
- enforce-delete currently runs protection before delete evaluation and returns both artifacts and guard result

Config note:
- runtime.compose.live_execution exists
- default is false
- false = write execution plans only
- true = attempt live backup command execution for supported adapters

